      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The view can be set to render a composition automatically when it is placed onscreen. The view stops rendering when it is placed offscreen. When not rendering, the view is filled with the current erase color. The rendered composition automatically synchronizes to the vertical retrace of the monitor. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you archive a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "QCView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, it saves the composition that’s loaded at the time the view is archived."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you want to perform custom operations while a composition is rendering such as setting input parameters or drawing OpenGL content, you need to subclass "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "QCView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and implement the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartz/qcview/1436256-renderattime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
